certs) - not because I needed the money - but it was fun (as well as the crew).\n\nI also got a goldfish at another booth that lived 8 years (amazingly for a kid caretaker).\n\nWhat's yours? \n\n*I'm not pissing on 250 but the run up to 1976 included 1975 and it was a hoot*", "author": "NewGoldenAge", "created": 1783161601046, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "NewGoldenAge", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "I know we tend to ragebait - but how about fun shit for the 4th? Current plans or fave memories. Go nuts. It's the 250th!", "last_comment_created": 1783167517165, "content": "<p>I'll start - in 1976 my folks (aerospace who moved every 2 years like a milbrat) sold (large) patriotic helium balloons in the park in UT in 1976. I'd do same for 30 years as a sideline (decorating for parades and rock concerts) - not because I needed the money - but it was fun (as well as the crew).</p>\n<p>I also got a goldfish at another booth that lived 8 years (amazingly for a kid caretaker).</p>\n<p>What's yours?</p>\n<p><em>I'm not pissing on 250 but the run up to 1976 included 1975 and it was a hoot</em></p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 13, "score_up": 26, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "\u00a0\u00a0AMERICA\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0FIRST\u00a0", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2073207271841050869", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ATBlv94AE", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 122,